WktGhL27vM7YmgMRBvttjRwJuyZOvjye1KRMOkL0DDGH9Qui6v1ZnKrrZpUectv6lJIMWkAfPcYaVd3_9sM1_t0vO0k9byFMR1G64y-Vb2JVH8_1i1Rz9Za2PDUfHNfXGYJo-yryI0QdiS02HWXfFjlNMZgBXCZxO7LxJpT6lm3DGTexcLPaeVc3SuJot3D-xgC-Jz4HAQhYK6Yxh7YyJwiw_DXldo3j8Ic2LjHPljnZahBKLLVP4ZgNBB1zWfx4CZ8vDE8ShgYTxRwZ8ogUVS-8nGpNgI_ji6lmCALyXOaQ3pe1n9CIs0je_Igfd3d6DCNEkbop8U318E1jZ0K8HuYu8fL1A5579xYkzoqxD3YL0OYDy6kAyNOyrah-1GHcrWRC-EZy-1fn-LRBzk16JR0rc_ctyt7PFQcu57yWcZ0drTJOKtSinrHYBj-MgvRdcAppiDlcUQiC01hhyOAnPqNk54slBmWFnH_kf9ufalmFDwAVlaUg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Vert.x and Netty Dependencies**\\n\\nI’ve found concrete evidence that Vert.x 5.0.1 depends on Netty 4.2.2.Final, just like 5.0.0. The existing test setup has runtime arguments restricted to 5.0.0 because Netty 4.2.x needs unsafe access on Java 25. It appears that for 5.0.1, I might need to set specific system properties for native testing. The question is whether to include version conditions for both 5.0.1 and 5.0.x. I still need to verify some details regarding the JDK property.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering OAuth2 Dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the risks involved with the OAuth2WebClient classes, which only compile with the optional `vertx-auth-oauth2` dependency when covering OAuth-specific scenarios. It might be best to avoid adding this dependency unless we’re intentionally testing OAuth2 integration. I also need to look into whether to include this optional dependency in the setup. My research shows that the POM lists it as optional. The driver can add dependencies before generating if necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Vert.x Web Client 5.0.1 is usable with in-process HTTP servers and no extra dependency or Docker image, but its resolved Vert.x/Netty stack still uses Netty 4.2.x, matching the existing 5.0.0 native-run workaround for Java 25.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runtime tests on JDK 25/current-defaults, ensure the test build applies the same runtime system properties used for Vert.x Web Client 5.0.0: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. The current 5.0.0 scaffold gates these args to libraryVersion == '5.0.0'; generated or repaired tests for 5.0.1 should include 5.0.1 in that condition or otherwise apply the properties for Vert.x 5.0.x native runs.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"OAuth2WebClient exists in the artifact but depends on optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2; meaningful core WebClient coverage does not require it, so avoid OAuth-specific tests unless an explicit test dependency is added.\",\n    \"Local Gradle/native-image verification remains authoritative; if Netty or GraalVM behavior changes, the system-property workaround may need adjustment.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_020eee790238761a016a4029ea8f588190bcb4d3c090747a99\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1033, "output": 926, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27559, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782589920373, "responseId": "resp_020eee790238761a016a4029e0d9688190a6e834c4b84f4966"}, "toolResults": []}
